Sentencas: Symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells (SSOFCs) possessing the same electrodes have attracted plenty of scientific interest for lots of advantages compared with conventional SOFCs with different anodes and cathodes.
Titulo: Tantalum doped La0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ electrodes for symmetrical proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this paper, a 10 mol% Ta doped perovskite-type oxide La0.6Sr0.4FeO3-delta, named La0.6Sr0.4Fe0.9Ta0.1O3-delta (LSFT), is studied as both an anode and cathode for proton conducting SOFCs (H-SOFCs) operated between 500 and 800 degrees C. LSFT is chemically compatible with a BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-delta (BZCYYb) electrolyte, even co-sintering at 1000 degrees C for 10 h. The activating energy (E-a) of electrical conductivity for LSFT is only 0.44 eV.
Titulo: Tantalum doped La0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ electrodes for symmetrical proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At 800 degrees C, the polarization resistances (R-ps) for LSFT barely reach 0.02 omega cm(2) in air and 0.1 omega cm(2) in H-2, and the corresponding E-a values are only 1.39 and 0.91 eV, respectively.
Titulo: Tantalum doped La0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ electrodes for symmetrical proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The peak power density (PPD) of a symmetrical H-SOFC (SHSOFC) using LSFT electrodes is 0.697 W cm(-2) at 800 degrees C. Herein, LSFT should be a promising electrode for SHSOFCs.
Titulo: Tantalum doped La0.6Sr0.4FeO3-δ electrodes for symmetrical proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells
